caption: Quick service for takeout and the food was delicious! :)
My experience was AMAZING! food is wonderful and the gentleman who helped me with the order was so nice and helpful! THANK YOU SO MUCH, for this amazing experience
Takeout was ready in ten minutes! Tasty too :)
Love Tom Yum! Their pad see ew is by far my favorite in the city and the lunch deals are amazing value. Very nice staff too.
One of my favorite places to eat in Lakeview.  Tom Yum Cafe makes some of the best Pad Thai that I've ever had.  I also like the atmosphere of the restaurant.

Ordered from Tom Yum via Grubhub tonight and the entire meal was horrible.  The massamum curry was NOT right at all. Grey dried out beef and a watery sauce. Not a hint of curry. Pad Thai was flavorless and topped with peanuts when asked to have them held.  Larb and Tom Kai were also disappointing. This restaurant does not know how to make good Thai at all.  Bad, bad, bad!  Grubhub should drop this restaurant.
delicious and very great food.

The staff and service was very friendly and they took excellent cleaning safety measures. We ordered Crab Fried Rice, Tom Yum Noodle Soup, and Pad Prik Khing which were all very flavorful with perfect blend of spices. If you want authentic Thai food in Lakeview I would highly recommend Tom Yum Cafe!
Great authentic taste, particularly with the namesake Tom Yum!! Actual galangal and lemongrass in the broth! It's our favorite in the area! Also try the boat noodles!
Pickup (takeout) experience has been fantastic. Delicious curries and extremely friendly staff!
Live near by and tried it 3 times before giving up. Never found a good dish
My go-to for amazing Thai Food in Lakeview. Delicious food and very nice staff.
Amazing!!
This place constantly delivers. They have fantastic food for convenient rates, there are no long waits even when the place is busy.

This place is so underrated. It’s sad that people don’t really see the restaurant because it’s around the corner .  The food is so flavorful. My favorite is the chicken basil and the papaya salad.  The prices are cheap. Try it!
The food was outstanding!!! We did the lunch menu for $10, so worth it! We ate indoors, seating wasn't very comfortable and service wasn't that great. I think they operate more as a take out...

We love going out. Yesterday we  visited this excellent place which friends told us about. We had a beautiful evening there with exceptional food and a well-trained stuff and a talented chief cook. We  added this venue in our phone list  and we will definitely return very soon. We deeply recommend.
Great Tom Yum. Very cozy. Limited seating. Very intimate but fantastic food and friendly staff

Would recommend fasting rather than eating here. Chicken larb was one dimensional in flavor. Pad Thai had virtually no taste at all. Even the peanut sauce on the Thai salad was not up to basically Thai takeout standards. Basil chicken was actually tasty, as was the mango sticky rice. But something made me ill.

BYOB. 12-seats.  Lots-n-Lots of authentic Thai Spicy Dishes! Neighborhood Place.  "No delivery as they only have 2 Cooks." 🥰 Untainted by Greed! 😉  Basic protein is INCLUDED with dish. 👏  $9.50 PAD SEE EW is a single serving. So, so THAI ICED TEA.  I look forward to coming back for more especially the Soups!
(Translated by Google) Cheap and tasty  (Original) Дёшево и вкусно
Amazing hole-in-the-wall Thai place. Good prices. Tasty food! Great place to bring a date for that intimate feeling. Would definitely eat here again.
Love the Thai basil Stir Fry!
Food tasted like absolutely nothing, I had ordered the pad Thai and Thai rice and got an order that tasted like nothing. Wouldn’t recommend this spot, I was left half sick afterwards.
a foodie , tiny ,hard to find place with excellent Thai food.cOnly 4 tables means that they make it all  fresh to order.
Tried red curry and eggplant basil stir fry! Both a must try.. Loved it!
Pricey but excellent

Fantastic. If you wanna feel ‘REAL’ thai food, you should go. Go twice. Go three times. Keep going. I haven’t eaten all the food they provide. But I assure that theirs are true one.  There were some people eating there like us. But there the people ordering foods to go, too.  I truly recommend you all to go.

TERRIBLE. Long wait only to be given the wrong order. Owner admitted it was their mistake but refused to replace it. Called twice to ask for a refund but was refused and ended up getting  screamed at by two different workers. AVOID.
The noodles we quite undercooked.
Best Thai food! Love the isaan sausage. Everything is tasty.
Its a small hole in the wall sort of a place. Best for takeout. We ordered soups, curry and a stir fry entree which were very good.
This place has the Real of Thia food . Is very Yummy Yummy

Pretty good stuff. Not very expensive, and service if you are ordering out. I wouldn't recommend treating this as a sit down place, rather a take out place. I would recommend the American Fried Rice the most, which has hot dogs, eggs and chicken wings in it, which is pretty good.
A hole in the wall with great tasting Thai food.

Tasty Thai food with hearty portion. The owner (who is also the chef) is a lovely Thai lady.  My favorites (so far) are their noodle items. Try boat noodles (noodle in pig blood broth-trust me, it tastes so much better than you would think) and ก๋วยจั๊บ 'guay jub' (flat noodle with sweet and salty broth topped with hard boiled egg, pork, etc). Guay jub taste just like what we have in Thailand! Sooo good.
just ok. Cozy atmosphere but much better Thai close by!
A friend from Thailand recommended this place but very very disappointed with the authenticity and overall taste.

One of the best thai food in chicago. Taste is authentic just like in Thailand. Every thing is delicious. It is quite spicy. The place is small, only 10 seats. You can reserve table in advance. It may be difficult to find street parking. Or you can go by red line, get off at Belmont and walk a little bit.
Amazing tasting thai food.
Very authentic Thai food, spicy and original ingredients
Cosy place with excellent food. Tastes just like Thailand :)
Delicious.  Amazingly huge menu for a tiny kitchen. Highly recommend

The fourth star is for the taste of the food. This place is pretty much middle of the road for me. I wouldn't say that its very different from the average american Thai offerings. They have a pretty decent lunch special, but the soup of the day depends on whatever they have in their kitchen. For me, the sauces and taste of the dishes had more authenticity than the average thai restaurant.  The place is small and I came here on a Saturday, and it was completely empty. However, given its size Im sure it fills up pretty quickly. They do take reservations. I would recommend calling in advance on the day you are going there since they have been closed a couple of times when I went. Also, when on Broadway, turn west onto Barry, they are the 3rd building down on the right.  the service was good- not too much english spoken, but efficient and helpful. The cook makes good
Awesome Thai food ... Yum Yum 🇹🇭

This Thai restaurant is small, but has seating for about 12 people.  The menu offers a large variety of dishes, which is great.  The food was pretty good, but some dishes were a miss.  Tod Mun Pla $6.50 – Small delicious fish cakes. Tom Kha soup $4.50 – Good and comes loaded with ingredients. Kai Jeow Ground Pork $7 – You can’t go wrong with Thai omelet. Pad Ped Pla Duk $12 – Catfish with just the right kick. Bamee Galic Chicken $9 – Not much to this dish other than noodles and chicken.  Not the bamee style I like. Mor Kang $4 – Pass on this dessert.  I’ve had much better Thai custard than this dry and bland one.  We were able to find paid street parking out front.
delicious Thai food. Small hole in the wall but great place for take out or quick lunch. The pad Thai and massaman curry were very good.
Their food seems watered down. . The curries and sauces are diluted. The portions, in comparison to other similar places has decreased.
There was a fly in my water. Set lunch menu was awful
We eat here quite often. The food is very delicious and authentic.  Consistently flavorful.
The restaurant is very small, but very tasty and authentic.
Their phone number doesn't work. I called multiple days and no one ever picks up.
Tiny little place with super friendly staff and reliable Thai favorites.

We ordered to deliver. I am a 45 year old family man with a culinary taste. First the hot and sour soup smelled. The fried rice was very greasy. The Chicken Sate was edible. The edamame was rejected by my kid. (she loves edamame) How can you mess up edamame!!!!!!!  Hope they fix this soon.
Food here is authentic.
Great Thai food , finally in our neighborhood!
Best Thai in town.
Very tasty food.  Very friendly. I don't think I have had a bad thing here.
The best authentic Thai food in Chicagoland!!!

This little hidden spot was a good find for me when I lived in the neighborhood. They were open later than other places for those late night munchies and their food is clean with good portion sizes. I was never disappointed.
Really good food that isn't heavy with the salty canned flavorings. Little sitting area if you want to eat in. Best take out Thai in the neighborhood :)

All of the food we got was WONDERFUL! My only complaint was that the portion sizes are pretty small for the price, so you may want to get an appetizer. The cashew chicken is AWESOME and so are the crank rangoon and pot stickers!
The Best Thai food on the Broadway!! Try their Cambodian fried rice!!
Great authentic food. Quite small with 4-5 tables, but the food makes up for it.

Food was great just only one time difference. I can give 4-5stat for food but open time I rate 1 star because i went there but restaurant still close maybe 7 times and make me so dissapoint. How they can do business with out permise time

Says they open at 11:00a. They do not. If they stick to their business hours as posted, they could have had our business. I guess they do not like making money. Or know how to run a business. On to the next place :)
Tasty-Tasty!

I USED to eat here a lot until I was served COLD CRAB RANGOON! Does this mean you don't make it fresh? Do you re-use old orders, put it in the fridge and then re-sell it? I paid to have extra seafood in my Tom Yum soup, the soup your restaurant is named after, and it came with almost none. I called back and spoke to a very nice woman who took my name and number and said I could come in another day and have my meal replaced. I called today to do so and the owner said that he wanted me to bring in the crab Rangoon from two nights ago! The woman I spoke to never asked such a thing. He would barely let me speak and said he didn't care and that he has other customers so he doesn't care about me. I would think twice about eating here. I never will again.

Very authentic Thai Food and it is very tasty!! We got Green Curry, Pad Se Eww, and Mango Sticky Rice. Made us reminisce about our recent trip to Thailand. I highly recommend if you're in the neighborhood!
So many good Thai restaurants nearby, but I was pleasantly surprised. Great Tom yum, loved the green curry. Will come back
Sweet staff and delicious food. Tom Kha soup is fantastic, the curries dont disappoint. Nice addition to the neighborhood.
